column9: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Unique Users)
column10: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through unpaid distribution. (Unique Users)
column11: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Unique Users)
column12: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Total Count)
column13: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's posts entered a person's screen through unpaid distribution. (Total Count)
column14: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Total Count)
column15: Lifetime: The number of unique people who engaged in certain ways with your Page post, for example by commenting on, liking, sharing, or clicking upon particular elements of the post. (Unique Users)
column16: Lifetime: The number of people who matched the audience targeting that clicked anywhere in your post on News Feed. (Unique Users)
column17: Lifetime: The number of clicks anywhere in your post on News Feed from the user that matched the audience targeting on it. (Total Count)
column18: Lifetime: The number of people who have given negative feedback to your post. (Unique Users)
column19: Lifetime: The number of times people have given negative feedback to your post. (Total Count)
column20: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your Page post to people who have liked your Page. (Total Count)
column21: Lifetime: The number of people who saw your Page post because they've liked your Page (Unique Users)
column22: Lifetime: The number of paid impressions of your Page post to people who have liked your Page. (Total Count)
column23: Lifetime: The number of people who like your Page and who saw your Page post in an ad or sponsored story. (Unique Users)
column24: Lifetime: The number of people who have liked your Page and clicked anywhere in your posts. (Unique Users)
column25: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed to 95% of its length without any paid promotion. (Unique Users)

column29: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed for more than 3 seconds without any paid promotion. (Unique Users)
column30: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed for more than 3 seconds without any paid promotion. (Total Count)

column41: Lifetime: The number of people who matched the audience targeting on the post that clicked anywhere in the post on News Feed, by type. (Unique Users)

column3:
Congratulations Fawz Mirza!!

Check out her series "You Should Know This By Now" on #weareotv: https://vimeo.com/channels/1362984

#AsianPacificAmericanHeritageMonth

Set across Chicago, 'the T' follows Jo and Carter, a young trans woman and queer Black man, as they learn how to be best friends in the wake of their romantic relationship and Jo's transition.

Join us for the world premiere of this revolutionary web series on June 18th at the Chicago Cultural Center. Doors open at 6:00pm and the screening will begin at 7:00pm. Following the screening will be a moderated discussion with co-creators and stars Bea Cordelia Sullivan-Knoff and Daniel Kyri Madison.

Miss us? On June 8th we will premiering an array of brilliant new works at Rebuild Foundation. One of the pieces is "Darling Shear", a docu-series by Diana Quinones Rivera that follows choreographer Darling Shear and her group of dancers: AaLiyah ChrisTina, Alix Schillaci, Andy Slavin, Rashida KhanBey-Miller, and Tila Von Twirl, as they explore their personal understandings of identity, expression, movement, and collaboration.

RSVP and find more information here: Open Television Premieres: New Black TV
Congrats to Stephanie Jeter, our head of production, on your recognition by the American Black Film Festival!

OTV - Open Television's Head of Marketing, Eli Micky is dabbling more and more with LIVE TV. Check out Untitled Intimacy, an interactive performance piece debuting next week at the Queer Biennial 2018: What if Utopia in LA and make sure to keep your eyes peeled for more LIVE content from OTV coming your way very soon.

The Middle East isn't a continent y'all. C'mon.

This is a donation based class, all donations benefit I Grow Chicago! Don't forget to RSVP, we'll see you there.

The class will be followed by a short tea reception (provided by Davids Tea) before attendees view the pilot season of Karla's "Yogma" tv series alongside show director, creative partner, and fiance, Barry Demetrius. Demetrius will also be taking photos during the yoga class.

FB event: Gypsy Yoga Presents: Vinyasa flow and Then a Show

Q: What would you say to queer artists who feel discouraged about their potential in this industry?

"Don’t wait for permission to tell your story. There are gatekeepers in the media who will devalue our stories. That doesn’t mean you can’t tell it yourself. I think that if we have a sort of grassroots television revolution, the gatekeepers will see the need for a shift in representation. " the T - Web Series co-creator Bea Cordelia Sullivan-Knoff

“We rarely get to see women, like black women, in college or post-college and just having them deal with just life,” [Director C.J.] Thomas said. “I just knew that it would not only be something that kind of helped me deal with my own issue of getting older, but also just knowing that it would be something I know so many other black girls would love" -Chicago Tribune

In honor of #AsianPacificAmericanHeritageMonth we're dropping some knowledge. 

Enjoy "You Should Know This By Now", a series of comedic PSAs from artists within our communities. Inspired by ‘The More You Know’ campaign, the current administration and Asians who think this is stuff you should know by now. Concept by Fawzia Mirza. 

Watch the full series here: https://vimeo.com/channels/1362984/. Other artists in the series include Vincent Rodriguez III of Crazy Ex-Girlfriend, Zahra Noorbakhsh of the #GoodMuslimBadMuslim podcast, comedian @Atsuko Okatsuka Comedian/Actress and many more!

The series, produced and developed by Full Spectrum Chicago and OTV - Open Television, centers on the stories of Chicago residents Jo, a white trans woman looking for intimacy and Carter, a queer Black man facing a conservative upbringing. - from the Into release. 

Read on for an interview with co-creators and stars, Bea Cordelia Sullivan-Knoff and Daniel Kyri Madison: https://bit.ly/2HLwqJl

Be a part of the magic and donate to their kickstarter to get this beauty funded: https://kck.st/2rf8Ttj
